race.description: Book For Christmas Raceday Sat 6th Dec Handicap
race.comment: Tough. LADY MASQUERADE (5) was outgraded at Ewan over shorter but missed a whisker here prior in a CL6 and that reads well for this. Has a handy 2kg claim today and is capable of using an inside gate. TURN BIRD (1) won a 70 here three back but has been plainer the last two. Raced a $2.60 favourite last time in Open grade at Bowen. Has a handy 3kg claim in easier and the blinkers applied for the first time. They might prove the difference. RICH DIVINITY (6) raced handy and was back to his best winning a 55 here a month ago. Draws inside and Cartwright in reunited. Has weight relief and that brings him into it. DEMON DELIVERA (4) resumes and has switched from the Geran stable in Toowoomba. He has won this trip and 2/4 first up. He's trialled at Rockhampton and the betting will be key.
